		<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
			<tr>
			<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=77545&amp;sid=75b09159c90aec4f268ddd1b7dc9c5b0#77545"><img src="templates/eqluclin/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Mon Aug 02, 2004 12:39 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: Re: DOOM 3 !!!</span></td>
				<td width="30%" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap" align="right"> <a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=77545&amp;sid=75b09159c90aec4f268ddd1b7dc9c5b0"><img src="templates/eqluclin/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td></tr></table></td>
			</tr>
			<tr><td colspan="2"><hr /></td></tr>
			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> I have yet to play any FPS that doesnt have mouselook that is even decent or in the same category as on the computer. IE - XBox and PS2 suck %@$# for FPS, IMO of course. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I used to think that, until I played Halo. I hated it at first; getting used to a dual-axis joystick was annoying and seemed wholly inferior to the mouse-keyboard combo I'd been using for fifteen years... but then, I'd been using m-k for fifteen years. Of course I liked it better.
<br />

<br />
After I beat Halo on Legendary for the hundredth time, I finally got the PC version of Halo. Using m-k for Halo on the PC sucks @#%$ %@$# compared to playing it with a dual-axis joystick on the Xbox. There's no comparison at all. I was very surprised by this, since my initial reaction was one of "finally, I can play it properly" and it became "wtf is going on here?"
<br />

<br />
Then there was Metroid Prime on the Gamecube. This annoyed me to no end because the dual-axis setup there is NOT the same as Halo, but once I was used to it, again I had no problems becoming my usual untouchable self using a dual-axis configuration.
<br />

<br />
Bottom line is that FPS works just as well with mouse-keyboard as it does with dual-axis. I think you get better aiming with the mouse-keyboard combo, but you get far superior movement and strafing control with a dual-axis joystick. If you can't seem to play the game using a dual-axis controller, stop whining and take some time to learn it and stop trying to play it like you are using a mouse-keyboard combo. It is more than adequate to play any FPS game. Upping the dual-axis sensitivity helps a lot; most of the problem for me was that turning took too damn long.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
	</tr>
